::Auto-run Script Setup::

Now we need to tell the operating system to run the script for the Pi user. In the command prompt or in a terminal window type :

$$ ---> sudo nano /etc/xdg/lxsession/LXDE-pi/autostart


Scroll to the bottom and add the following line :


$$ --> 
	@xset s off
	@xset -dpms
	@xset s noblock
	@python3 /home/pi/Desktop/Plant_project/chktrigger.py


where “/home/pi/Desktop/Plant_project/chktrigger.py” is the path to your script.

Type “Ctrl+X” to exit, then “Y” to save followed by “Enter” twice.


::To check process type in:: 

$---> ps aux | grep chktrigger.py

::To kill process::  

$---> kill <PID>